		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2"><a name="105608117615143"></a><span class="msgSubject">few notes on bard aggro</span><br clear="all" />
		   <span class="sm">Posted: Jun 20th  2003 at 12:34am EDT<span class="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/db/item.html?item=11706;mid=105608117615143#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a> </span></span></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" class="mform" ><span class="fs8"><span class="notbold">By: </span><a href="/db/poster.html?user=234823"><span class="">buvasthebard</span></a><b><span class=""></span></b>
		   <br /><span class="nobr"><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Default  </span><br />
<br/><a href="/db/item.html?item=11706;page=1;howmany=50#105608117615143"><img alt="" title="Use this to create a link to this post" src="/shared/garrowrt.png" border="0" height="9" width="11" /> Link to this post</a>
<br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1" alt=""/></span></td>
<td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>As a 57 bard, I can say that while we will never be #1 in either aggro or dps, we are up there.  Yes, our melee dps sucks due to lack of dual wield.  Yes, because of this our melee aggro sucks.  However, as I found out tanking around the castle in PoD (now there was a challenge for a guy with &lt;1k ac and 2.2k hp), we can generate hella aggro with the right songs, and these same songs put me over 100 dps, which is ungodly for a bard if he wants to live in most groups :P.  If I was slowing and bardnuking I could hold aggro pretty well.  I wasnt the best tank, but we didnt wipe ever and I held aggro for most of the fights.</p>
</td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td class="fs8"></td><td align="right" class="fs8" >1 reply</td></tr></table></td></tr></table>
